# Cron Architecture (audric side)

t2000 server runs the cron schedule (ECS, `node-cron`). Audric exposes internal endpoints under `/api/internal/*` that the cron POSTs into. Each endpoint owns a domain and writes to one set of Prisma models.

## The endpoints

| Route | Writes | Triggered by |
|---|---|---|
| `POST /api/internal/financial-context-snapshot` | `UserFinancialContext` | 02:30 UTC |
| `POST /api/internal/portfolio-snapshot` | `PortfolioSnapshot` | 02:00 UTC |
| `POST /api/internal/memory-extraction` | `UserMemory` | 03:15 UTC |
| `POST /api/internal/profile-inference` | `UserFinancialProfile` | 03:00 UTC |
| `POST /api/internal/chain-memory` | `ChainFact` | 04:00 UTC |
| `POST /api/internal/payments` | `Payment` (status updates) | On chain event |
| `POST /api/internal/health-factor` + `hf-alert` | sends Resend email when HF < 1.2 | Indexer hook (real-time) |
| `POST /api/internal/notification-users` | (read-only) | t2000 cron lookup |
| `POST /api/internal/user-address` + `app-event` | misc internal lookups | Various |

## Auth — every internal endpoint MUST check `x-internal-key`

```typescript
// apps/web/lib/internal-auth.ts
import { env } from '@/lib/env';

export function assertInternal(req: Request) {
  const key = req.headers.get('x-internal-key');
  if (!key || key !== env.T2000_INTERNAL_KEY) {
    throw new Response('Unauthorized', { status: 401 });
  }
}

// apps/web/app/api/internal/financial-context-snapshot/route.ts
export async function POST(req: Request) {
  assertInternal(req);
  // ... do the work
}
```

**Never** assume "internal" means "no auth needed because it's only called by ECS." Vercel functions are public HTTPS endpoints; the auth gate is the only security boundary.

## Idempotency — every endpoint MUST be safe to re-call

Cron WILL retry. Use upserts, not creates:

```typescript
// ✅ Idempotent
await prisma.userFinancialContext.upsert({
  where: { userId },
  create: { userId, snapshot, computedAt: new Date() },
  update: { snapshot, computedAt: new Date() },
});

// ❌ Not idempotent — second call creates duplicate row
await prisma.userFinancialContext.create({ data: { userId, snapshot } });
```

## Sharding — required at 1k+ DAU

Single-endpoint fan-out (process all users in one POST) hits Vercel function timeout (10s pro / 60s pro+) at scale. Accept optional `{ shard, total }` body params:

```typescript
const body = await req.json().catch(() => ({}));
const { shard, total } = body as { shard?: number; total?: number };

const users = await prisma.user.findMany({
  where: shard != null && total != null
    ? {
        // hash-based shard filter — id is cuid, hash to a number 0..total-1
        id: { /* shard predicate */ },
      }
    : undefined,
});
```

Default shard count is **8**. Driven by the t2000 cron — see `t2000/.cursor/rules/cron-job-architecture.mdc`.

## Response shape — uniform across endpoints

```typescript
return Response.json({
  created: 100,
  skipped: 50,
  errors: 2,
  total: 152,
});
```

t2000 cron logs the aggregate counts; deviation from this shape breaks cron observability.

## What MUST NOT happen

```typescript
// ❌ Internal endpoint that hits Sui RPC per user
for (const user of users) {
  await suiClient.getAllBalances({ owner: user.suiAddress });  // 10k calls = rate limit
}
// — batch via BlockVision OR go through the canonical getPortfolio (it caches).

// ❌ Internal endpoint that writes to multiple domains
// — financial-context shouldn't also update UserMemory. One job, one domain.

// ❌ Internal endpoint that responds with HTML / a redirect
return NextResponse.redirect('/some-page');
// — internal endpoints are JSON-only.

// ❌ Skipping the auth check
// — lib/internal-auth.ts is one line; use it.

// ❌ Long-running synchronous work inside a route
// — split the work into shards and let t2000 fan out.
```

## Adding a new cron-triggered endpoint

1. Create `app/api/internal/<job>/route.ts`.
2. `assertInternal(req)` first line.
3. Accept optional `{ shard, total }`.
4. Make it idempotent (upsert).
5. Return `{ created, skipped, errors, total }`.
6. Add the t2000 cron job (see `t2000/.cursor/rules/cron-job-architecture.mdc`).
7. Update `prisma-models-overview.mdc` if it writes to a model not yet listed there.

